HEADWORD: Monotonist
<hw>Mo*not"o*nist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who talks in
the same strain or on the same subject until weariness is
produced.</def> <rj><au>Richardson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monotonous</ent>⟦br⟧
